# Define your data transforms
transform = transforms.Compose([
    transforms.Resize((32,32)),
    transforms.ToTensor(),
    transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406],
                         std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
])

# Load the ImageFolder dataset
dataset = ImageFolder(path, transform=transform)

# Shuffle the dataset
indices = torch.randperm(len(dataset))

# Define the split sizes 80%,10%,10% respectively
train_size = int(0.8 * len(dataset))  
val_size = int(0.1 * len(dataset))
test_size = len(dataset) - train_size - val_size

# Split the dataset into training, validation, and test sets
train_indices = indices[:train_size]
val_indices = indices[train_size:train_size+val_size]
test_indices = indices[train_size+val_size:]
train_dataset_ct = torch.utils.data.Subset(dataset, train_indices)
val_dataset_ct = torch.utils.data.Subset(dataset, val_indices)
test_dataset_ct = torch.utils.data.Subset(dataset, test_indices)
trainloader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(train_dataset_ct, batch_size=32,
                                          shuffle=True, num_workers=2)
valloader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(val_dataset_ct, batch_size=32,
                                          shuffle=True, num_workers=2)

# function to perform histogram equalization on a PyTorch tensor
def convertToHistEq(tensor):
  x_train_hist = tensor.detach().numpy()
  array = []
  for a in x_train_hist:
    image = np.transpose(a, (1,2,0)) 
    image = cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    image=np.array(image, dtype="uint8")
    image = cv.equalizeHist(image)
    image = cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)
    image = np.transpose(image, (2,1,0)) 
    array.append(image)
  array = np.array(array) 
  x_train_hist = torch.tensor(array,dtype=torch.float32)
  return x_train_hist

# function to perform Adaptive histogram equalization on a PyTorch tensor

def convertToAdHistEq(tensor):
  x_train_hist = tensor.detach().numpy()
  array = []
  for a in x_train_hist:
    image = cv.normalize(a, None, 0, 1.0, cv.NORM_MINMAX, dtype=cv.CV_32F)
    image = np.transpose(image, (1,2,0))
    img_clahe = exposure.equalize_adapthist(image, clip_limit=0.03)
    image = np.transpose(img_clahe, (2,1,0)) 
    array.append(image)
  array = np.array(array) 
  x_train_hist = torch.tensor(array,dtype=torch.float32)
  return x_train_hist

HOG Feature descriptor¶

In [ ]:
## function to perform HOG feature extractor image array
def hog_svm_features(image):
    image = np.transpose(image, (1, 2, 0)) 
    feature = hog(image, orientations=9, pixels_per_cell=(8, 8), cells_per_block=(2, 2),block_norm= 'L2', channel_axis=-1)
    return feature
In [ ]:
## function to convert tensor to array
def toHog(tensor):
  array = []
  x_train_np = tensor.detach().numpy()
  for arr in x_train_np:
    f = hog_svm_features(arr)
    array.append(f)
  array = np.array(array) 
  return array

## function to perform HOG feature extraction and histogram equalization on a PyTorch tensor

def toHog_histeq(tensor):
  array = []
  # Convert PyTorch tensor to NumPy array

  x_train_np = tensor.detach().numpy()
  for arr in x_train_np:
    # Transpose the image from PyTorch tensor format (channels first) to NumPy format (channels last)
    image = np.transpose(arr, (1,2,0)) 
    image = cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    image=np.array(image, dtype="uint8")
    # Perform histogram equalization on the grayscale image
    image = cv.equalizeHist(image)
    image = cv.cvtColor(image, cv.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)
    # Transpose the image back to (channels, height, width) format
    image = np.transpose(image, (0,1,2)) 
    feature = hog(image, orientations=9, pixels_per_cell=(8, 8), cells_per_block=(2, 2),channel_axis=-1)
    array.append(feature)
  array = np.array(array) 
  return array

In [ ]:
#function to perform HOG feature extraction and adaptive histogram equalization on a PyTorch tensor
def toHog_adhisteq(tensor):
  array = []
  x_train_np = tensor.detach().numpy()
  for arr in x_train_np:
    # Normalize the image to the range [0, 1]
    image = cv.normalize(arr, None, 0, 1.0, cv.NORM_MINMAX, dtype=cv.CV_32F)
    image = np.transpose(image, (1,2,0))
    # Perform adaptive histogram equalization on the image using the CLAHE algorithm
    image = exposure.equalize_adapthist(image, clip_limit=0.03)
    image = np.transpose(image, (0,1,2)) 
    feature = hog(image, orientations=9, pixels_per_cell=(8, 8), cells_per_block=(2, 2),channel_axis=-1)
    array.append(feature)
  array = np.array(array) 
  return array
In [ ]:
x_train_arr_adhisteq = toHog_adhisteq(x_train)
x_val_arr_adhisteq = toHog_adhisteq(x_val)
In [ ]:
x_test_arr_adhisteq = toHog_adhisteq(x_test)

Creating CNN Model¶

In [ ]:
#https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/ai/windows-ml/tutorials/pytorch-train-model
class cnn(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self,dropout=0):
        super(cnn,self).__init__()
        self.dropout = dropout

        # Defining convolutional layers and batch normalization layers
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(3, 64, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban1=nn.BatchNorm2d(64)

        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(64, 64, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban2=nn.BatchNorm2d(64)

        self.conv3 = nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban3=nn.BatchNorm2d(128)

        self.conv4 = nn.Conv2d(128, 256, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban4=nn.BatchNorm2d(256)

        self.conv5 = nn.Conv2d(256, 256, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban5=nn.BatchNorm2d(256)

        self.conv6 = nn.Conv2d(256, 512, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban6=nn.BatchNorm2d(512)

        self.conv7 = nn.Conv2d(512, 512, 3, 1, 1)
        self.ban7=nn.BatchNorm2d(512)

        # Defining pooling layer, dropout layer, and average pooling layer

        self.pool = nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2)
        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(self.dropout)
        self.avgPool = nn.AvgPool2d(2,2)

        # Defining fully connected layers

        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(512*4*4, 4096)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(4096,4096)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(4096, 2)

        self.softmax = nn.Softmax()

    def forward(self, x):
    # Apply convolutional and batch normalization layers, followed by pooling layer
      x=F.relu(self.ban1(self.conv1(x)))
      x=self.pool(x)

      x=F.relu(self.ban2(self.conv2(x)))
      
      x=F.relu(self.ban3(self.conv3(x)))

      x=F.relu(self.ban4(self.conv4(x)))

      x=F.relu(self.ban5(self.conv5(x)))

      x=F.relu(self.ban6(self.conv6(x)))
      x=self.pool(x)

      x=F.relu(self.ban7(self.conv7(x)))
      x=self.avgPool(x)

      x = x.view(x.size(0), -1)
      
    # Apply fully connected layers and dropout layer
      x = F.relu(self.fc1(x))
      x = F.relu(self.fc2(x))
      x = self.dropout(x)
      x = self.fc3(x)
      return x

val_ds = TensorDataset(x_val, y_val)
# creating skorch based cnn classifier with all initial parameters
cnn_net1 = NeuralNetClassifier(
    cnn(),
    max_epochs=100,
    lr=1e-3,
    batch_size=32,
    optimizer=Adam,
    train_split=predefined_split(val_ds),
    optimizer__weight_decay=0.01,
    criterion=torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss,
    device=device,
    callbacks=[
        EarlyStopping(patience=5, monitor='valid_loss')
    ]
)

val_ds_histeq = TensorDataset(x_val_hist_eq, y_val)

    cnn(),
    max_epochs=100,
    lr=0.01,
    batch_size=32,
    optimizer=torch.optim.SGD,
    train_split=predefined_split(val_ds_histeq),
    optimizer__weight_decay=0,
    criterion=torch.nn.CrossEntropyLoss,
    device=device,
    callbacks=[
        EarlyStopping(patience=5, monitor='valid_loss')
    ]
)

    (ban4): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv5): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban5): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv6): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban6): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv7): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban7): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (pool): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
    (dropout): Dropout(p=0, inplace=False)
    (avgPool): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0)
    (fc1): Linear(in_features=8192, out_features=4096, bias=True)
    (fc2): Linear(in_features=4096, out_features=4096, bias=True)
    (fc3): Linear(in_features=4096, out_features=2, bias=True)
    (softmax): Softmax(dim=None)
  ),
)

    cnn(),

    (ban4): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv5): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban5): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv6): Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban6): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (conv7): Conv2d(512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (ban7): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (pool): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
    (dropout): Dropout(p=0, inplace=False)
    (avgPool): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0)
    (fc1): Linear(in_features=8192, out_features=4096, bias=True)
    (fc2): Linear(in_features=4096, out_features=4096, bias=True)
    (fc3): Linear(in_features=4096, out_features=2, bias=True)
    (softmax): Softmax(dim=None)
  ),
)

plt.colorbar()
tick_marks = np.arange(2)
plt.xticks(tick_marks, ['Negative', 'Positive'], rotation=45)
plt.yticks(tick_marks, ['Negative', 'Positive'])
plt.tight_layout()

plt.xlabel('Predicted label')

# Add numbers to the plot
thresh = cm03.max() / 2.
for i, j in np.ndindex(cm03.shape):
    plt.text(j, i, format(cm03[i, j], 'd'),
             horizontalalignment="center",
             color="white" if cm03[i, j] > thresh else "black")
plt.show()

# defining parameter range

              'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.0001],
              'kernel': ['rbf','poly','sigmoid']} 
  
grid_svm2 = GridSearchCV(svm.SVC(probability=True), param_grid,verbose=10,refit=True,cv=2)
  
# fitting the model for grid search
grid_svm2.fit(x_train_arr_histeq, y_train_arr)

              'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.0001],
              'kernel': ['rbf','poly','sigmoid']}

# fitting the model for grid search
